label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 412: Risālah fi al-ʻamal bi-al-kurah ... etc.
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Three astronomical treatises: the first and third are on the astrolabe (the third illustrated with several diagrams), and the second is more generally on astronomy.
        Language: Arabic
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: Paper, 18; 1¹⁸; no foliation marked on leaves.
        Layout: Written in 27 long lines.
        Script: Written in Ottoman naskh script, with titles in a larger naskh script.
        Decoration: 9 astronomical diagrams (f. 14v, 15r, 16r-18v) in red and black ink in third work; titles in green ink; significant words or phrases in red or green ink.
        Binding: Marbled paper, Arabic inscription including date of Safar 950 in ink on upper cover.
        Origin: Written in Cairo in A.H. Safar 950 (May-June 1453; f. 1r, 18v, upper cover).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 412
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 4827043 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/4827043
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs412.html
